    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We can make it not impact the production build by giving the errors in `if (process.env.NODE_ENV === \"development\")`, which can be filtered out in webpack with either:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nnew webpack.DefinePlugin({\r\n  'process.env': {\r\n    NODE_ENV: JSON.stringify('production')\r\n  }\r\n}),\r\n```\r\n\r\nor\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  new webpack.EnvironmentPlugin({\r\n    NODE_ENV: 'development', // use 'development' unless process.env.NODE_ENV is defined\r\n  }),\r\n```\r\n\r\ncombined with uglify.\r\n\r\nSee as well how [react](https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/optimizing-performance.html#use-the-production-build) does it.",
